---
title: Configuring Ops Manager Director for vCHS and vCloud
---

Refer to the following procedure for help configuring the Ops Manager Director for VMware vCHS and vCloud product tile.

1. Log in to Pivotal CF Operations Manager.

1. Click the **VMware vCloud Hybrid Service** tile.

    <%= image_tag("vchs-tile.png") %>

1. Select **vCHS/vCloud Director credentials**, enter the URL of the vCloud Director and your credentials, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vcloud-credentials.png") %>

    **Note**: This user must have create and delete privileges for VMs and folders.

1. Select **vCloud configuration**, specify the datacenter name and storage profile name, and
click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vcloud-configuration.png") %>

1. Select **Network configuration**, enter the network name, subnet, Pivotal CF IP ranges, DNS, and
Gateway settings, and click **Save**.
The Pivotal CF VMs will use the IP range you specify.
**Reserved IP Ranges** are blacklisted from the installation.

    <%= image_tag("vcloud-network-config.png") %>

1. Select **NTP servers**, enter a comma-delimited list of time server
addresses, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vcloud-ntp-servers.png") %>

1. Select **System Settings**, check or uncheck **Enable VM resurrector
plugin**, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vcloud-resurrector.png") %>

1. Select **Resource Sizes**, accept the defaults or make necessary changes, and
click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vcloud-resources.png") %>

1. Click the **Installation Dashboard** link to return to the Installation
Dashboard.

